caption: listen.. I've been here about 5 times already since coming to the city. and it is definitely one of my go-to places as it transcends traditional udon. yes, it still has your favorite classic udon soups. but their specialty ones like the sea urchin or salmon spinach are so sooo good!! the portions are pretty huge but comfortingly filling. I'd say this place deserves more stars than it has!
Best sushi I've ever had
The best sushi in Chicago ! Love their rolls and they also have a nice wine selection. I’ll be back soon!
Delicious sushi -- amazing and friendly service. They also always have the best music playing -- usually 90s rap and hip hop. Outside dining with heaters.
My favorite location for Japanese food. looking forward to returning with my friends. the place has a cool atmosphere.
(Translated by Google) Authentic Japanese food Great value for the price  (Original) Autentica comida japonesa Excelente relación calidad/precio

Nice place to have sushi. They arranged the place to have kind of protections between table, to have social distancing. The service is good, the food is very good. The menu is not very big but enough to have different tastes of japan.
Excellent calamari. Cocktails were will made. Sushi was also excellent. Tried the black rice and it was pretty good.
First time trying black rice anything, it was amazing! Highly recommend their sampler platter!
You're welcome
Ordered from Union Sushi and waited for 3 hours only to have the order cancelled. They never answered their phone or updated us on anything. Very frustrating do not order from here.
Friendly staff, nice mix of foods at a very reasonable price. Covid safety protocols all seem to be in order - screens between all tables indoors.

One of my favorite sushi spots in Chicago, all the classic rolls you'd expect with some fun innovations added in. My favorite roll is the spicy tuna but the new godzilla roll was fantastic. Highly recommend Union Sushi if you're looking for a delicious modern sushi meal.
After 4.5 years of living in Chicago I finally found the best sushi, enough to make me write a review

Great Atmosphere, attentive staff. Food was fresh and came out in a timely manner for how busy it was. The duck was good but REALLY could have been rendered a little more properly. Portions are on the smaller side.
japanese food, yeah, delicious. Looking forward to a return trip.
Staff was super helpful, the sushi rolls were even better.  The girl at the front was extra sweet to us. Our server was great as well, would highly recommend it!
Good sushi!!
I constantly stop grabbing some food in here. I like the quick customer service and well made dishes. Kudos.
The sushi here never fails to impress. Love coming here. Will def recommend
Awesome food and drinks !!! 😎😎
Fantastic sushi & fun ambience. Our server was attentive & helpful. Will definitely return

Food was decent, but plates (miso salmon, truffled tuna) are very small. Also it's really loud since it's next to the L train. I would recommend the seafood ramen--it was the one item that was a large portion size, great value, and delicious!
Vegetarian Friendly. Good service.
username: Just a Fashion Girl from Chicago

caption: What a disappointment! I have been going to Union Sushi for over 5 years, it's always been a favorite for date nights, gathering with friends and I even took a couple of my clients for dinner there. After my last visit (Aug 30), it is safe to say, that I will not be returning. I am not sure what happened to friendly service, cool ambiance, but most sadly, the quality, presentation and price of food. Simple rolls, like spicy tuna, for over $15! These used to be priced at under $10, on top of it, they now are at a grocery store level. Prices have jumped 75%-100% since the last time I visited, and it is just not worth it.

Wow this sushi place is just amazing!! I went here with my boyfriend for lunch and we both loved the atmosphere, our waiter was super nice and the food of course was delicious!! I recommend the shrimp tempura roll and the lamb chops. Definitely would eat here again!

From the first moment  you come to that place  they give you a nice feeling. Very congenial team, it is a happy restaurant to to go out with your friends or with your date. heavenly  cuisine, professional  chef de cuisine, comfortable  pay and professional  service. Warmly recommended.
Excellent food. We tried all the specials, plates were enough to share ! Our waitress was friendly and attentive. They have outside seating.  Tables are spaced appropriately.
Good place 👍
This sushi is comparable to sushi sold at the grocery store. Very overpriced and the rolls were small. the service was good. Wouldn’t return

Had a dinner reservation in February during All Star Weekend.  It’s a great atmosphere. Our waiter, Javier was great! He was very pleasant and he knew the menu very well! Everything he recommended was on point! The portions are perfect and delicious!  We took advantage of some of the specials, I had two Moscow mules and my husband had Sake. I was pleasantly surprised by the oysters! They are a must try! Trust me, you’ll not be disappointed!  We really enjoy our visit and will be going back for sure!
Great food and service

Do no go here anymore. They have increased the prices to a ridiculous amount for food and booze. $15 wine glasses of wine in a plastic cup. Sushi served on cheap paper plates. Spent double what it should’ve been
(Translated by Google) Very gud  (Original) Very gud
Great hospitality & the food is so fresh. Sushi delicous. Try the exotic skewers as appetizers.
The best Sushi I ever had. Don't miss out on Sushi with scallops!
This place is worth visiting. They have large portions for affordable prices. Regularly neat and with excellent vibes. Would recommend to others.
Great food. Great place. One of my favorites in all of Chicago.

I like to go with friends to this place with my warmest recommendations. I visit this restaurant often. This recommendation is always successful. The dishes they serve are yummy and the crew is generous and cooperative. always when we visit this place we pass a lovely time.  highly recommended.
As always, they never disappoint. Daniel always humble and greets everyone with a smile! The crew always attentive and we're always treated like Family. We come here every Friday!!!

I ordered through the app and received my good 30 mins after the estimated time. People who came in to order in person after me received their food before me. I was in a rush and thus decided to plan ahead. The girls there were trying to be nice but I was extremely dissatisfied with my experience. What's the point of ordering ahead if it wasn't going to work? I could've just ordered when I arrived and I would have been happier.

I joined Fitness IL purely because of the pool they had. I also used the services of Taiko Wong for swimming lessons and massages. She is a great teacher and over the course of an year, she taught me how to swim pretty well (I did not really know how to swim before that).Her massages are even better and I would highly recommend her services.

Had such a great meal last year we came back again. Aside from feeling like a scene from the Blues Brothers where every rushing El-train caused a roaring pause, we went back. The service was again exceptional as we went again for happy hour. The oysters with a mild jalepno counterpoint and some slivers of fried (scallops?) were incredible, and the tuna with mushroom counterpoint was also marvelous. We had such a wonderful meal we came back again 2 days later and again loved it. An easy walk from almost anywhere along or near the Miracle Mile. The ambiance was good, the service wonderful and everyone was friendly. We recommend it highly and plan a return when next in Chicago
Nice, trendy ambiance. Excellent service and tasty food.
Poor value - nice presentation
Pretty good value but I food was just average

I work across the street from Union and what a treat it is. My coworkers and I frequent this place for Happy Hour. The Moscow Mules are awesome, as is the sushi special and oysters (if you like them)! We always have great service - thank you to Nina (who I see most often) as well as the wonderful hosts, kitchen staff, and attendants. See you soon!

Food is delicious! And place looks very modern. You could go there for romantic meal or just with a group of friends - it works perfectly both ways. Meals are not very big, but not painfully small either. Mushroom salad and rainbow roll were very good. If you are into asian cuisine it's definitely place to go!

Had the opportunity to have dinner with my son and sushi is one of his favorites. Got there before 630 to take advantage of the specials. Started with the house sake and oysters. They had a citrus, vinegar, spice mix that was outstanding. Vote them the best oysters ever at this point. Then ordered the black rice sushi special, made up of four different rolls. Great flavor, great with the black rice. Followed up with the Pacific roll and the Union roll and we were stuffed.
I visit this spot a lot since I work close by. I love how the service is always awesome and they keep the place neat at all times. Prices are affordable and they serve big portions.
Great food and drinks. Friendly staff.
The place is wonderful and roomy, the menu was yummy and the prices were very affordable. fast, efficient service and very amiable staff members. I highly recommend this place.
They offer a fantastic range of fresh food. I loved dining here. Staff members are always very friendly, prices are reasonable and the spot is always neat.
Very neat and convenient restaurant. They offer large portions and for reasonable rates. We enjoyed the food a lot and the waiters were super amiable and explanatory. I recommend this place.
Overpriced but then again it's Starbucks. Wish there were more independents in the area

Had to wait 30 minutes for a table... even though we were seated a table that was empty the entire time we were waiting. Rude and unprofessional! Served miniature sized appetizers for the price of a premium entree. Not sure when "beef filet" translated to "beef on a stick".
You’ve got to try the oysters

We made a reservation for 8:00 pm and had to add two people well in advanced during the afternoon. They annoyingly told us it will then maybe be an 8:30 pm reservation. We got there at 8:00 and they sat us by the bar, next to an empty table. We had to wait at the bar until 8:30 till they then sat us at the empty table. Their pettiness threw us off. Not going back.
Not a big fan of sushi

Came in for a light snack and cocktails.The nigiri was touching, but it was fresh enough that the flavors didn't mix to much. The dragon roll was excellent. The bartender was so great, and so were the drinks.

We love eating out. Yesterday we  found this magnificent restaurant which friends recommended to us. We spent a lovely time there with first-rate dishes and a professional team and a distinguished  chef. We put this fine restaurant in our list  and we shall no doubt go again very soon. We warmly recommend.

We visited Union Sushi on NYE! We were sure to have reservations, obviously. They were running a little behind, which we didn’t mind, so we had a few drinks at the upstairs bar while we waited. Once we got to the table, we were told we would receive some free appetizers. Little did we know we would have some of the best service we have ever had! The hostess noticed everyone wasn’t eating one of the free apps and she sent another appetizer over. Everyone was BEYOND AMAZING!!!! We would recommend Union Sushi in a heartbeat. Not only was the experience amazing, the food was also! THANK YOU!!!
Attended a birthday celebration here, and enjoyed the entire experience. Great food. Fun atmosphere, and great drinks.
Finest food, friendly staff, consistently excellent mood. They charge fair rates and the food quality is fantastic. Fantastic work.
Great food, very helpful and accommodating staff.
Definitely a place worth stopping by, the food is good and well prepared, the pricing is fair and it is constantly clean here. Highly recommended.
Overpriced and just not that worth it. Sake was pretty good on happy hour which is why it’s 3 stars for me
Good was sooooo good! Went during happy hour and it was totally worth it. Definitely going back.
Absolutely a place worth stopping over, the food is great and well prepared, the cost is convenient and it is always well organized there. Great work.
Great happy hour
This place is worth giving a shot. They have big portions for fair rates. Constantly well kept and with good atmosphere. Highly recommended.
Very fresh sushi. Great oysters and hand rolls. We where also lucky enough to enjoy fresh real wasabi ground at the table. Definitely coming back next time I’m in Chicago
I just loved their dishes. I always get good customer service there. The place is clean and the cashiers are always helpful. Would recommend to others.
Upscale, modern sushi bar. Offers great happy hour specials, good for a dinner date. I usually come for lunch, and they always have me out in under an hour. Really cool place, fair prices.
Food was terrible
Hip place, great food friendly staff
The menu and service were ahead of my expectations. We surely enjoyed the environment of this place. Fantastic spot to take my family out for lunch.

It was... Not that good... i ordered from the bbq section, scallops were good, red meat was all overdone, lamb chops were overpriced and very skimpy. Chicken Katsu appetizer for $12 was better than $40 of BBQ sampler. So disappointed. I was so looking forward to eating here too.
Good place!
Amazing food !!!
Great atmosphere and DELICIOUS 😋 MOSCOW MULES
Amazing food and service. A must!
It’s always amazing! Love this restaurant especially the BBQ menu. Best place for sushi in River North Chicago!
Good Atmosphere, food is well presented.... But for some reason the wow factor was not there. Sushi is excellent, Oysters wayy to small.  Prices are a bit high.
Great date/pub atmosphere! Food was 10/10, will go back!
OOOOHHHMYGOD. Union is amazing. The sushi and drinks are all delicious.
Sushi good
Chef Chao is the best!!
Filet skewers and oysters at happy hour are legit
Rigo the Sushi chef was great.
Warm service, tasty rolls, excellent happy hour -- all in a room kind of stuck in the late 90's/early aughts. Highly recommended, still!

It's okay.....I really liked our waitresses service and atmosphere. I found the rice for the sushi to be not very satisfying and the meats to be flavored fine but often dry. Luckily it's not really that expensive. The scallop dishes were great, but the king crab lacked a little intensity. Comparing this to Roka down the street, I'd probably go to Roka.

I had an average experience here. In terms of atmosphere, they play a lot of rap music, which is odd for a sushi restaurant. Our edamame was cold, and the service was quite slow. But the spicy tuna roll was delicious!
I really liked their food. I always get great service here. The place is always clean and the staff members are always very welcoming. Will come back again.
Ordered the lamb chops and what came out was hilariously small. Like the world's smallest lamb had a even smaller baby lamb. I enjoyed the flavor of my two 1.5 ounce "lamb chops"

The food was great ambiance was cool service was great through the meal but a little slow in the beginning and in the end for the check. It was a Saturday night however so it's understandable hence five star
Good food! Not amazing, but good. It seemed like their "wow" factor was more important than rich flavors.
Fresh sushiiiiii❤️

I'm here countless times since 2012 and still come here. Best chef table in this city. Everything delicious here. Always new house specials. Fantastic cocktails best house sake. Can't go wrong with happy hour here.
Dined here last night and the sushi is top notch.
Is always great,we go for what we like most of the times.
Decent food.  Cool spot.
Delicious food, fun atmosphere. Train passing by can make it difficult to hear.
They have a decent happy hour special on weekday (half price bubbly wines). Sushi is good. Atmosphere is fun/trendy.
Second time here and enjoyed the food and atmosphere.
Great for big parties. Service is fast, happy hour is worth it. Great music

Fantastic food and equally good if not better customer service by all! Ate here with a large group last night and forgot to increase my party number when I modified our reservation. Gia, Alondra and Karla were extremely accommodating and did everything they could to get us seated as quickly as possible. I also had the privilege of meeting Director of Operations Michael Lacson, who has helped me previously and goes above and beyond to ensure customer satisfaction. Our entire party was very impressed by the cocktail menu and we had such a fun evening. Thank you, Union Sushi, for a great evening!

I'm a big fan of the unique flair that they add on their dishes. A little extra zing and some Latin inspiration makes for tasty tasty food. I've only done sushi here but it's fun to get seated right away at the bar and watch the magic of both the sushi being prepared and the awesome sight/smell/sound of their robata grill.  Happy Hour specials are decent but limited selection, and the Happy Hour is a little short for an after work bite.  However, I'll definitely be back to enjoy.
The food is always fresh and the staff always welcoming!

Wonderful menu with tons of fun and tasty items. I often seem to order something out of my comfort zone here, and it always turns out delightful. The decor is very modern and urban, with a Japanese flair. Thanks to the relaxed atmosphere and great staff it's really easy to feel comfortable at Union Sushi.
Service wasn't great, sushi was fairly good, but there's better options nearby
Loved it
Too salty
Amazing food !!
Had a good time here! Good food and service.

Underwhelming, especially when I really wanted to like it. Ramen was nothing special, meat was unflavored, it was not bad, it just was forgettable.  If this review helped you please thumbs up it.  Need to win a bet.
Awesome service, green tobiko with quail egg, black rice sushi, HH, cocktails, you can't miss out on the menu.
Good food, nice staff, nice decor
Overpriced, slow serves and small portions

Tables were very close together. Appetizer (raw tartare) got to the table after our barbeque selections. Scallops were small and not very flavorful. Whitefin Tuna steaks were good. Quail was the best dish. Wagyu tartare was very onion-y and lacked any interesting spice. Edamame is served room temperature (a style that some may like) and they were trying out a sour cream and onion salt. Hopefully they stick to just regular salt. In the future. Drinks were good though a bit pricey. All in all, a nice experience but there are better places in Chicago for the same price.
Great sushi, great staff, great specials

This place has a cool atmosphere and great food! We visited for Happy Hour and enjoyed their filet beef skewer, spicy shrimp sushi roll, and the truffled tuna.. which was incredibly good. We also had several glasses of sparkling rose and the mussels. I have to say, the mussels broth was so amazing. My wife embarrassingly stared at me as I shamelessly ate the broth like it was soup. Overall, great experience and we’ll be back.

It is one of our favorite River North go to places for BBQ and sushi. Bento boxes are particularly good for lunch. Pleasant neighborhood place, friendly staff. Highly recommend black rice samplers. Prices are rather reasonable for River North area.
One of my favorite sushi places in Chicago! A must!!!

Really good place for high end and fun sushi and maki rolls. Not just that they have very good grill foods.  They have a live grill and some of the best food.  Their offerings on the sake are great too. They have a wide variety of dry to fill bodied sake. They have good Japanese beer too.
Don't eat sea food but if I did I would definitely try this spot, I was only there to pick up a delivery
My fave sushi place ever!! Always a must stop when we visit Chicago. Great drinks and atmosphere too. Try the black sushi rolls :)
A favorite place for tasty Japanese food. There was fast and courteous service. Prices that won't break you.
Diarrhea for days
Wonderful menu and staff. Everything was delicious and presented with care.
Great food and urban, hip Atmosphere. Small portions but the flavor makes up for it
Pretty good food. Liked the interesting BBQ.
We went for the advertised happy hour. Enjoyed the oysters and the tuna. The dishes had an interesting fusion of flavors. Excellent and attentive service. Great casual and modern atmpisphere.

Awesome sushi and BBQ restaurant. Food was amazing and the wait staff was even better. Would highly recommend for anyone in the area or visiting. Everything is made there minutes before you enjoy it. Also there were plenty of drinks to choose from!
Amazing menu, really unique items.  Sushi was fresh.  Only drawback is that it is pricey but worth the try

The sushi is nice and fresh. The drinks are great and the music is popping. It seems like they have biggie smalls radio station playing on Pandora. If youre getting rolls get them wrapped in black rice. It's not much of a taste difference but it's fun, cool and different. The service is great. One time I broke a glass and they were super considerate. They even comped my drinks.
Excellent food, prompt service
Great Sushi and food! Their Happy Hour is not only a great deal, but a lot of fun.

They have a happy hour. This is always a plus if any of your party is having drinks. The prices drastically increase after happy hour However the drinks are made with top shelf liquor. The drinks also pack a punch! I was with a large party and no one left any food on thier plate. That says a lot about the preparation.   Everyone was satisfied. I  would  recommend!

Union Sushi is one of my favorite places to eat sushi in Chicago. It has very authentic food in a modern environment. Great cocktails and amazing sushi. Try the black rice rolls. They are hard to find, and delicious!
I've been here twice with my company. The food is satisfying and the service is kind, although I wouldnt recommend the ramen.
Dragon roll highly recommended.
Amazing rolls in upbeat environment.

Highly recommend happy hour here.  The Zakuro mule was delicious - maintained the elements of a classic Moscow mule but with enough of a twist to distinguish itself.  The oysters were a great deal (only $1.50 each!) and also well garnished. The beef filet skewer was tasty, though admittedly nothing too unique.  But the absolute stand out was the tuna tatami, which was PHENOMENAL. I loved its simple yet elegant presentation. The red pepper provided a great spice to compliment the tuna and avocado.  I'll definitely be back!
Delicious branzino and soup.  My friend loved the soft shelled crab.  Drinks very tasty!

(Translated by Google) High quality sushi, with happy hour in food and drink until 18:30. Some delicious manhattans.  (Original) Sushi de gran calidad, con hora feliz en comida y bebida hasta las 18:30. Unos manhattans deliciosos.

Good deals on happy hour, although the information in website is diferent from the menu at the restaurant. It is more expensive there, so not nice. Spicy shrimp had the right amount of spice for my taste, truffled tuna was good (could be better!), beef skewer was tender. My sparkling rosé was very good! The enviroment is inviting for happy hour but train station is very close to the place, so sometimes the L disrupted the conversation.
Excellent service.  Great menu. Tasty food!
Had a damn good time. Food and service is excellent. Looking forward to going again 😊

Tantalizing Sushi and BBQ. We went for the samplers and weren't disappointed at all. Meats tasted great and the special sushi rolls just made our day. The service was quick and the place had an upscale vibe to it. Would definitely recommend if you are looking for fine dining options in river north. However, make sure you out down a reservation for weekends.
I keep coming back for the happy hour oysters - so light and fresh and memorable.
This place is the real deal. From the sushi, to the Yakitori this place checks all the boxes. My fave was the snow crab and veggie wrapped rolls.
My favorite sushi spot in Chicago
A preferred place for tasty Japanese food. The service was very friendly and kind. This place has a great design.

Came with 5 of my friends late to our reservation and have to leave early to catch the show and those people at union shushi were just amazing , they went above and beyond to bring us the food early even though we ordered like 10 different things . From the bar b q sampler to the seafood ramen noodle and from the mussels to the duck wing , oysters on the shell and more . Everything was amazinggggggggg. Will defiantly be back .

Be sure to make reservations for this popular Gold Coast hot spot, as wait times on busy nights  may exceed one hour. We asked our server/bartender for favorite dish and sushi recommendations. His picks were fantastic. Don’t miss the mussels and be sure to “upgrade” at least one or two of your sushi rolls to include the black rice. Seating at the upstairs bar was close but comfortable. We would be happy to dine here again.
Typical sushi joint. Probably slightly better than your other Thai/Sushi joint. I would come back again for a casual meal but wouldn't call it a gourmet place.
japanese food, super delicious. This place does it for me. The service here is attentive. This place has a nice atmosphere.
Wildly overpriced for incredibly mediocre sushi. There are dozens of better sushi places in the city
Great food and atmosphere. Service is top shelf.
Great atmosphere,  fun energetic , great cocktails and good food
Food was fantastic...lunch service was a bit slow.
Really unique sushi options. Great happy hour
Cold food, super small portions that are extremely overpriced.
Excellent food and service!
This place has an incredible menu. I will be back and I recommend it to all. Prices are also reasonable.
Really great sushi our server was awesome.
Food is amazing and not as expensive as I anticipated. Their hot sake is why I'm coming back.
Way overrated and too expensive for what you get.
Very good Sushi and a awesome twist on barbeque!
I have been in too many sushi places. Not tasty
Great Sushi!!!
Great happy hour specials. Good service. All the wine was great too.
Awesome Sushi. Definitely have to try the grilled king crab legs
Amazing
Great service and the Happy Hour specials were worth it!
Absurdly small portions and waiters don't point this out when you order.
Excellent sushi, the service was great. Prices are little bit high.
Great selection! Good happy hour deals
Great service.  Food was amazing.
Excellent food

A nice little spot to grab some food. I started with  the miso soup which was very good. Then had the black rice sushi sampler. I was surprised how quickly it was served, but it was very good. The atmosphere was nice. The grill is right in front so everyone can what's being cooked, but its behind glass. So you don't have to worry about the flames. The music was a mix of 90s hip hop and r&b, and some other stuff. The music was low enough that you can carry on a conversation, but loud enough to hear. I will definitely go back again.
Ever time I go there I am satisfied 😉
Really good sushi and very good service. A bit high on the prices, but would definitely go back - maybe for happy hour specials!
Amazing food, great vibe in the place as well.
Great Sush! Great appetizers! Great service!

Great food and service.  They overcooked the lamb but was still tasty.  The alligator ribs were incredible.  The kangaroo was a good experience as well.  Fresh wasabi refreshing! Definitely coming back.
What a place!  Highly recomended

One of my favorite stops of the weekend! I was surprised this place wasn't busier!  The best sushi I have had in a long time, hands down! I was very intrigued with the black rice so we ordered the sampler and was blown away.  The drinks were creative and very tasty also staff was friendly and attentive. We had counter seats and had fun watching the itamae work their magic!  I was so preoccupied enjoying the food I didn't take a single photo... there is always next time.
My favorite sushi place
Great food and drinks! Would return!
Seafood lovers discover taste of fresh...
Amazing. Best sushi, great atmosphere, friendly staff. Really good happy hour.
Try the Devon roll. My fav.
Great place to entertain, good food, interesting menu, good drinks including japanese whiskey selection, lots of fun.
good food
Best sushi I've had ! I've had terrible experiences with the calamari but it was great here! The Japanese whiskey Toki was great as well!
Great robata and sushi.  Love the uni shooters and happy hour oysters.
The food is exquisite! It's also delicious. The environment is elegant.
Always incredible!

I've downgraded my rating based on my last time there. I've frequented this place for years and feel like the quality and flavor of the food has declined. The duck yaki-soba was my favorite dish. Last time I ordered it, it was dry and starchy. They definitely didn't put enough kotsu sauce in it and has been consistently getting drier and starchier over time. The happy hour oyster prices have gone up(fine), but they didn't put any of the crispy onions in them. Prices have increased, but quality has decreased.
The food was very underwhelming, and my server seemed annoyed that I took awhile to order even though it was after the lunch rush and the place was empty.
My favorite sushi place besides Nobu
Excellent sushi! They off half off drinks during happy hour. I recommend the calamari roll, best sushi roll I had in Chicago.
Been there already a couple of times and yesterday celebrated my bday there. The decor is modern and stylish, the staff is great and the food is amazing. Definitely will be coming back more often.
Great destination. Good Service. Fun food and drinks. Happy hour before dinner was a + too! Half price drink specials and deals on apps.
Great atmosphere and two bars makes it feel way less crowded! Great prices as well!
Our favorite dinner spot! Our usual waiter (now manager) Tenon takes care of us every time and when we can't get him, the entire staff is incredible, so nice, and has the best recommendations.
Hot staff and boozy drinks
The Best!
Delicious place! Everything we got was super tasty  specially a Lychee Martini ♡

I go here pretty regularly for happy hour (4-6:30pm). I love how attentive the wait staff and bartenders are. They are really awesome! They always ask if you have any allergies and everything comes really fast. The beef skewers are really yummy and a great appetizer. They have free edamame when you sit down. Even when there are a lot of reservations I can always find space at one of the three bars. The sushi is SO DELICIOUS. Really high quality.
great place to chill with friends, eat sushi and have drinks.
Was my Birthday. They made us feel very special. Great happy hour specials. Awesome sushi.
Just go here, please. Amazing food, high quality ingredients and creative cocktails. The interior is very modern and young. Make a reservation, though! This place gets packed on the weekends.
Japanese fushion with lot of strong flavor.
Nice place for sushi and ramen in Chicago!
Food was excellent happy hour oysters are only 1.50 each. And mules are 5.00 great atmosphere and music was good. Dont miss out on this place....
Amazing happy hour selections!

Chef Chao is a one of a kind in the kitchen. Every item on the menu is a complete winner. My friend and I had the pleasure of sitting in front of Chef Chao for our first time there. He helped us with the menu gave unreal recommendations and told us about a new dessert that wasn’t even on the menu yet. One of the barbaque items we got was the king krab legs which Chef Chao recommended we get spicy and I’m telling you I could’ve ordered 22 more of that same dish. Thank you Chef for the amazing experience and we will be back very soon!! Highly recommend!!!!!!

Poor service. waited 30 min just to place an order with our waitress,the meat was raw in he sampler we received. Waitress never came around or anyone for that matter so we could mention it to anyone. Over priced.
Decent sushi and nice grilled items. Happy hour is really good. Good vibe
The chefs here are truly artists and the service is impeccable!
Best fried calmari I have had in the USA.  Sushi was awesome too.

This is the ultimate in sushi experience. Union is an upscale restaurant offering food from three kitchens: sushi bar, bbq's bar, and Japanese kitchen. The bbqs station sits in the middle of the restaurant, grilling roberta-style meat and seafood. Grill crab is my favorite. Grilled steak fillet is nice and tender. Union also serves spirits  and cocktails.  Awesome experience!!!

This place is a nice Japanese restaurant that serves ramen, sushi, and grilled food. The atmosphere is nice and everyone is pleasant.  Mushroom Ramen: What I got this time around was the Mushroom Ramen. It actually doesn't explicitly say what kind of broth and tare it was, but going by the taste and color, I'm going to assume it was a shoyu ramen. It was very light and refreshing as vegetarians tend to be. Topped with three kinds of mushrooms, fried onions, sprouts, green onions, pickled chilis, tofu, seaweed, gobo (some sort of root), and cabbage, this ramen had no shortage of toppings. Everything on there was very delicious. Seasoned perfectly and having a good distinct flavor (except for the tofu, I was actually a little disappointed with that). One mistake that's on me is way too much chili oil. I dumped the whole container they gave me and it ended up being a bit too spicy for me. Regardless, I did enjoy it. The noodles were firm and straight. Great all around and with a plethora of great toppings and great tasting broth this ramen did not disappoint. I will definitely come back to try their other ramens.  Beef Cheek Ramen: So I came back here like I said I wanted to last time! This time I got thier Beef Cheek Ramen! Again, they don't explicitly say what kind of broth it uses, but I went off taste and it seemed like it was a beef broth based shio ramen. The toppings consisted of pulled beef cheek, green onion, ginger, tofu, fresh chilis, tomatoes, parmesan cheese, and shredded cabbage. Their online menu also says it should have had shiitake mushrooms, but I did not see or taste any in there. Let's start with the broth. Honestly, it was pretty bland. They completely underseasoned, and besides for the beefy flavor, it did not really have much else going for it. I was hoping for a bit more since I'd never had a beef broth based ramen before. Onto the noodles themselves. Again, nothing really special going on here. They were a bit soft and the word I want to use to describe them is flimsy. No bounce or spring to them at all, but they tasted fine at least. The toppings though is where this ramen shined. The beef cheek was absolutely amazing, as was the fried tofu. The fresh veggies were also great. Chilis has become one of my favorite veggetables toppings on ramen. The online menu said that the tomatoes should have been roasted, but I don't think that was the case in my bowl. Regardless they were good as well. And then finally the parmesan cheese. I'm pretty sure it was a gimmick more than anything. Didn't really add much as it was just kind of a blob in the middle. Overall, the ramen was alright. After the vegan ramen last time, I was really hoping this meaty one would be at least as good, but unfortunately that was not the case. I'll still definitely be coming back though. Just not for this bowl. That Pig Tail Ramen looks quite intriguing... Besides the ramen though, I ended up being charged more than the online menu said the bowl cost. That left a sour taste in my mouth even though it wasn't much. Overall, this visit has dropped my score of this place by one star.  Seafood Ramen: As are Union's other bowls, this is one unique bowl. The Seafood Ramen bowl has a mellow seafood broth topped with mussels, fried calamari, napa cabbage, shrimp, chilis, and scallions. Let me tell you right now they do not skimp on the toppings here. Plenty of mussels, a nice pile of fried calamari, and a couple shrimps. I had more than plenty to eat. On top that, every one of those toppings were absolutely delicious. If I had to make one complaint, it would be that the calamari was a bit too salty. The broth itself was very mellow. Not strongly fishy at all as you might think a seafood broth might taste or smell. Instead it was more fresh ocean tasting. Salty and with just a hint of the seafood it was cooked with, it was absolutely wonderful. The noodles here were firm, straight noodles, which is my preferred kind so those were perfect too.

Union Sushi is a must for anyone. I came during the peak of the lunch hour, while rushing because I was on my own lunch break, and the servers were slammed. Now, in most respects that would be considered a restaurant's "perfect storm." I didn't feel an ounce of that hectic energy during my meal. My server, Tnon, was amazing, incredibly helpful and attentive even though he had a lot on his plate, the food was delicious and came out in a very timely manner, and the atmosphere was relatively tranquil considering how many people were eating. Even the sushi chefs behind the sushi bar were friendly and engaging. I highly recommend both the Tempura Plate as a starter and the Black Rice Sushi Sampler. The flavors span the whole spectrum from bright and playful to unctuous and indulgent. Union Sushi was able to take a set of circumstances that would sink most other restaurants, and not just rise above those circumstances, but create a top notch customer service experience that will have me coming back again and again. Don't walk. RUN to Union Sushi.
